n><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Shelter </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">analysis</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://odi.dwp.gov.uk/disability-statistics-and-research/disability-facts-and-figures.php#ho"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://odi.dwp.gov.uk/disability-statistics-and-research/disability-facts-and-figures.php#ho</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220154/eia-social-sector-housing-under-occupation-wr2011.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/220154/eia-social-sector-housing-under-occupation-wr2011.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Burnip v Birmingham City Council &amp; Anor [2012] EWCA Civ 629 (15 May 2012)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">MA &amp; ors v Secretary of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">State for Work and Pensions QBD 30.7.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">3</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/bedroom-tax-ray-hope-thousands-2263218"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/bedroom-tax-ray-hope-thousands-2263218</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn13"></a><a href="#_ftnref13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Significantly higher </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">numbers of Habinteg tenants formally meet the criteria to be deemed as under-occupying but either do not receive Housing Benefit or are exempted because they are over state pension age.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn14"></a><a href="#_ftnref14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Arrears 2012-13 is 5.6 per cent of total rent owed, with 4.45 per ce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nt of this being arrears owed by current tenants. Source: Annual Report to Tenants 2013, Habinteg Housing Association.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn15"></a><a href="#_ftnref15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.papworth.org.uk/downloads/makingdiscretionaryhousingpaymentsworkfordisabledpeople_130710181752.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.p</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">apworth.org.uk/downloads/makingdiscretionaryhousingpaymentsworkfordisabledpeople_130710181752.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn16"></a><a href="#_ftnref16">[16]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.dwp.gov.uk/docs/universal-credit-service-charges-guidance-landlords.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.dwp.gov.uk/docs/universal-credit-service-charg</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">es-guidance-landlords.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn17"></a><a href="#_ftnref17">[17]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Ibid.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn18"></a><a href="#_ftnref18">[18]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Letter from DWP to Habinteg, 20 February 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn19"></a><a href="#_ftnref19">[19]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Disabled Facilities Grants in England: A Research Report, Astral Advisory for the District Councils’ Network and the Society of District Council Treasurers, April 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn20"></a><a href="#_ftnref20">[20]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Habinteg Tenant Satisfaction Survey data</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn21"></a><a href="#_ftnref21">[21]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.jrf.org.uk/publications/impact-localising-council-tax-benefit"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.jrf.org.uk/publications/impact-localising-council-tax-benefit</span></a></p></body></html>